@xSayPleasex You're right. I haven't played in months, so I was a little iffy on the "growth" but I specifically mean stats of the character you play as. Unlocking more stuff was cool, I did like that, but it's still primarily random and based on luck. And my luck, especially, is awful. I recall countless times when I was doing well in a run, making actual progress, and then BOOM, terrible randomized room or item I picked up that killed me within a minute or less. Then I'm back at the beginning with little to no real progress outside of a new item I MAY or may not pick up down the road.

I simply prefer the Rogue Legacy approach of your character levels and stats and abilities constantly improving as you keep playing. RL makes the game very reasonable for hardcore fans of rogue-like and even more "casuals" like myself, as you don't HAVE to level up your character if you don't want to. I leveled up everything from strength to health to magic to double-jumps and mid-air dashing, and those things helped me SO much that I actually managed to beat the game, unlike Isaac where I lost to Mom once and that angered me enough not to play since.

But yes, Rogue Legacy is a great game and has a TON of replayability with NewGame+, NewGame++, and so on, each one significantly harder than the last. I just started up NG+ and holy crap, hard, lol, so yes, definitely check it out if you're interested.
